    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Hi Molly,</></>I have been an avid reader of your blog for the last year and just love reading your posts! I absolutely love corn and wanted to suggest that you visit a restaurant called &#8220;Al di la&#8221; the next time you visit NYC (<a href="http://www.aldilatrattoria.com" rel="nofollow ugc">http://www.aldilatrattoria.com</a>) . It is in Park Slope, Brooklyn and while everything they serve is simply masterful (think the trattoria in &#8220;Big Night&#8221;), their Tortelli with Corn filled with fresh sweet corn, mascarpone, and truffle butter is truly one of the most heavenly things I have ever eaten. </></>Thanks for the recipe&#8211; i will try using it before the good corn goes away&#8230;.</p>
    </div>

